  "body": "**What happened**:\r\nPod in graceful termination (Readiness: True, Status: Terminating) still shows up in the ready addresses section of related Endpoints objects. \r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nPod in graceful termination should show up in the unready addresses section of related Endpoints objects.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nSet up service and point to pods that can handle graceful termination. Watch related Endpoints object while deleting a backend pod. \r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n- The code to determine whether a pod should be in endpoints object is as follows:\r\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/release-1.8/pkg/controller/endpoint/endpoints_controller.go#L563\r\n- I am not sure whether users are relying on this broken behavior.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\nkubernetes HEAD",
